@node "Document_2" "Usage       "
The program should be started as a CLI door and this is the template: MClock
[LOCATION] -[MODE] *[CHAR] /[TEXT] where LOCATION is the only one that GOT
to be there. LOCATION is, as you might understand, where the user is logged
in. MODE can be one of: o - original mode d - digital mode t - thin digital
mode CHAR is the character to use in the numbers (default=#) and TEXT is a
text that should be displayed as a little note. Shouldn't be longer than a
couple of lines since the screen will otherwise flow ower.

Here are a couple of example usages:

"MClock Halmstad -d *- /dh0:text", will display the location as Halmstad,
the numbers with digital font and using the letter "-". It will also display
dh0:text as a note.

"MClock Sweden -t", will display the location as Sweden, the numbers will be
digital font and using the letter "#".
@endnode

